# Tooltips — never use `title`

Do **not** use the native HTML `title` attribute for hover hints anywhere in the UI.

```tsx
// BAD — native browser tooltip
<button title="Disabled">…</button>
<span title={`Minimum ${count} projects`}>…</span>
```

Native `title` tooltips are inconsistent across browsers/OS, delay awkwardly, cannot be styled, and are poor for touch.

## Use a custom tooltip instead

Use the shared `Tooltip` component in `app/components/tooltip.tsx`:

```tsx
import { Tooltip } from "@/app/components/tooltip";

<Tooltip label="Disabled" className="h-7 items-center text-amber-700">
  <i className="fas fa-poo text-[12px]" aria-hidden />
</Tooltip>
```

Do not copy raw tooltip markup — extend `Tooltip` if global behavior or styling must change.

## Still allowed

| Use | OK? |
|-----|-----|
| `aria-label` on icon-only buttons | Yes — accessibility name, not a hover tooltip |
| React prop named `title` (e.g. `AdminPanelSection title=`) | Yes — page/section heading, not HTML `title` |
| `<title>` in SVG | Yes — graphics metadata |
| Next.js `metadata.title` | Yes — document title |

## When adding hover help

1. Wrap the trigger in a `group/…` container with `relative` and `cursor-help` when appropriate.
2. Render tooltip text in a child with `role="tooltip"`.
3. Show on `group-hover` and `group-focus-within`.
4. Do not add `title="…"` on the same element.
